' State Diagram 06 — Validator lifecycle.
'
' Tracks a single validator's state across the slashing protocol:
'   Bonded → Equivocator-Suspect → Equivocator-Recorded →
'   Slash-Pending → Slashed → Removed
'
' Each transition is labeled with the detector output or PoS event that
' fires it. This is the canonical state machine the EquivocationDetector
' and PoS contract jointly implement.
'
' Source of truth for Figure 6.1 in slashing-specification.md.
'
' Render:
'   plantuml -tsvg docs/theory/slashing/diagrams/06-state-validator-lifecycle.puml

@startuml 06-state-validator-lifecycle
!theme plain

skinparam state {
  BackgroundColor<<unbonded>>   #ECEFF1
  BackgroundColor<<bonded>>     #C8E6C9
  BackgroundColor<<suspect>>    #FFF7EE
  BackgroundColor<<recorded>>   #FFE0B2
  BackgroundColor<<pending>>    #FFCDD2
  BackgroundColor<<slashed>>    #D7CCC8
  BackgroundColor<<removed>>    #B0BEC5
  BorderColor #444444
}
skinparam defaultFontName "sans-serif"
skinparam defaultFontSize 11

title Validator lifecycle in the slashing protocol

' Edge color legend:
'   green  (#2E7D32) = honest progression / bond entry
'   red    (#C62828) = adversarial action triggers transition
'   orange (#E65100) = detection / record-creation effect
'   amber  (#FF6F00) = recovery from failed slash
'   purple (#6A1B9A) = PoS Rholang slash invocation
'   gray   (#37474F) = terminal exit

[*] -[#2E7D32]-> Unbonded

state Unbonded          <<unbonded>>    : "(v, eₖ) — pre-bond lifetime.\nepoch tag eₖ is assigned on the\nnext successful bond deploy."
state Bonded            <<bonded>>      : "(v, eₖ) — bonded lifetime;\nbond > 0 (Bug #5 / T-9.5);\nslash authorisation scoped\nto epoch eₖ (§15.1)."
state EquivocatorSuspect <<suspect>>    : "(v, eₖ) — documentation-only.\nDetector saw 1 of 2 conflicting\nblocks. In Rust, code transitions\nBonded → EquivocatorRecorded\ndirectly in one atomic step."
state EquivocatorRecorded <<recorded>>  : "(v, eₖ) — EquivocationRecord\npersisted in tracker store"
state SlashPending      <<pending>>     : "(v, eₖ) — SlashDeploy emitted\nby a proposer; not yet executed"
state Slashed           <<slashed>>     : "(v, eₖ) — Bond zeroed\n(allBonds[v] := 0).\nProjection of the atomic\nstateUpdateCh! at PoS.rhox:473-482."
state Removed           <<removed>>     : "(v, eₖ) — Removed from\nactiveValidators (same atomic\nstateUpdate as Slashed; the two\nare not separately observable\nin the implementation but are\nlisted separately to match spec §6)."

Unbonded -[#2E7D32]-> Bonded : Bond deploy succeeds\n(@PoS!("bond", …)) —\nlifetime tag eₖ assigned

Bonded -[#2E7D32]-> Bonded : honest activity\n(propose, validate, etc.)

Bonded            -[#C62828]-> EquivocatorSuspect : detector observes\nconflicting block_2 by self
EquivocatorSuspect -[#E65100]-> EquivocatorRecorded : insert_equivocation_record\n(seqN-1, ∅)

EquivocatorRecorded -[#E65100]-> SlashPending : next proposer's\nprepare_slashing_deploys\n(authorised invalid-block evidence\nindex per Bug #14 / T-LivenessGap)

SlashPending -[#6A1B9A]-> Slashed : PoS @"slash" succeeds\n(allBonds[v]:=0;\nstart of atomic stateUpdate)
Slashed      -[#6A1B9A]-> Removed : same atomic stateUpdate\nremoves v from activeValidators\nand purges committedRewards
SlashPending -[#FF6F00]-> EquivocatorRecorded : slash deploy fails\n(transfer FIXME, fix #4)

Removed -[#2E7D32]-> Unbonded : new bond deploy\n@PoS!("bond", …)\n→ fresh (v, eₖ₊₁) lifetime\n(stale (v, eₖ) evidence does NOT\nauthorise slashing on (v, eₖ₊₁)\nper Bug #13 / T-9.12)

note right of EquivocatorRecorded
  Bug fix #2 (T-9.2) ensures the
  transition into this state is
  atomic under concurrent insertions.
end note

note right of SlashPending
  Bug fix #4 (T-9.4) ensures a deterministic
  failure path back to EquivocatorRecorded
  if the Coop-vault transfer fails.
end note

note bottom of Bonded
  Bug fix #5 (T-9.5): a stake-0 bonded
  validator should be impossible —
  enforced by assert(stake > 0) in PoS.
end note

note bottom of Slashed
  Slashed and Removed are retained as
  distinct lifecycle states matching
  spec §6, but in the implementation
  they are projections of the same
  atomic Rholang stateUpdate at
  PoS.rhox:473-482. They are not
  separately observable; the
  Slashed → Removed transition is
  conceptually instantaneous.
end note

@enduml
